@startuml afls_input_to_ahls_high_beam_permit_signal_flow
!theme plain
skinparam backgroundColor #FFFFFF
skinparam defaultFontName Arial
skinparam defaultFontSize 11
skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center
skinparam responseMessageBelowArrow true

title AFLS Input To AHLS High Beam Permit Signal Flow\n(AFLS state + vehicle speed -> AHLS assist and high-beam permit)

participant "AFLS state /\nvehicle speed" as LightCtx #F4F7FB
participant "AHLS\nheadlamp assist owner" as AHLS #E8F7E8
participant "AHLS state bus" as AhlsBus #FFF4CC
participant "Observers / lighting users" as Obs #E8F0FE

== Lighting Inputs ==

LightCtx -> AHLS : aflsMode / beamPattern / levelStep\nvehicleSpeed
AHLS -> AHLS : if AFLS stale then\naflsMode = 0 / beamPattern = 0 / levelStep = 0
AHLS -> AHLS : if vehicle stale then\nspeed = 0
AHLS -> AHLS : assistState = (aflsMode > 0) ? 1 : 0
AHLS -> AHLS : highBeamPermit = (speed >= 50 and beamPattern <= 2) ? 1 : 0
AHLS -> AHLS : glareCutLevel = levelStep/2 + permit bonus
note right of AHLS
Representative gating inputs
- aflsMode / beamPattern / levelStep
- vehicleSpeed
end note

== AHLS Publish ==

AHLS -> AhlsBus : frmAhlsStateMsg\nAhlsAssistState / HighBeamPermit / GlareCutLevel
note right of AHLS
Representative outputs
- AhlsAssistState
- HighBeamPermit
- GlareCutLevel
end note

== Downstream Visibility ==

AhlsBus -> Obs : headlamp-assist readback /\nlighting consumers

note over LightCtx, Obs
Representative runtime chain
1. AFLS state and vehicle speed reach AHLS
2. AHLS decides assist activity and high-beam permission
3. AHLS publishes glare-cut and permit state
4. Lighting observers consume the effective headlamp-assist posture
end note

@enduml
